This paper deals with caching and offloading in device-to-device (D2D) communication, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses energy consumption and optimization, which falls under information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions simulations and evaluation, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
